Step 1: Set Up Criteria

We have four criteria:

Cost (₹ crores) – lower is better

Completion Time (years) – lower is better

Experience (number of projects) – higher is better

Local Employment (%) – higher is better

We want to normalize all these values to a 0–1 scale where 1 = best possible value, 0 = worst possible value.

Step 2: Gather Raw Data
Bidder	Cost	Completion Time	Experience	Local Employment
L1 (Medi Health)	790	4.5	8	45
L2 (Care Well)	815	6	12	80
L3 (Life Line)	875	5	6	60
Step 3: Normalize Each Factor
3.1 Cost (Lower is Better)

Formula:

Normalized Cost
=
Max Cost – Bid Cost
Max Cost – Min Cost
Normalized Cost=
Max Cost – Min Cost
Max Cost – Bid Cost
	​


Max Cost = 875 (L3), Min Cost = 790 (L1)

L1: (875 – 790) / (875 – 790) = 85 / 85 = 1

L2: (875 – 815) / 85 = 60 / 85 ≈ 0.706

L3: (875 – 875) / 85 = 0 / 85 = 0

✅ This makes sense: lower cost = higher normalized score.

3.2 Completion Time (Lower is Better)

Formula:

Normalized Time
=
Max Time – Bid Time
Max – Min
Normalized Time=
Max – Min
Max Time – Bid Time
	​


Max Time = 6 (L2), Min Time = 4.5 (L1)

L1: (6 – 4.5) / 1.5 = 1.5 / 1.5 = 1

L2: (6 – 6) / 1.5 = 0 / 1.5 = 0

L3: (6 – 5) / 1.5 = 1 / 1.5 ≈ 0.667

✅ Lower completion time = higher score, aligns logically.

3.3 Experience (Higher is Better)

Formula:

Normalized Experience
=
Bid Experience – Min Experience
Max – Min
Normalized Experience=
Max – Min
Bid Experience – Min Experience
	​


Max = 12 (L2), Min = 6 (L3)

L1: (8 – 6) / 6 = 2 / 6 ≈ 0.333

L2: (12 – 6) / 6 = 6 / 6 = 1

L3: (6 – 6) / 6 = 0 / 6 = 0

✅ Higher experience → higher normalized score.

3.4 Local Employment (Higher is Better)

Formula:

Normalized Employment
=
Bid Employment – Min Employment
Max – Min
Normalized Employment=
Max – Min
Bid Employment – Min Employment
	​


Max = 80% (L2), Min = 45% (L1)

L1: (45 – 45)/35 = 0/35 = 0

L2: (80 – 45)/35 = 35/35 = 1

L3: (60 – 45)/35 = 15/35 ≈ 0.429

✅ Higher employment → higher score.

Step 4: Overall Score (Optional Weighted Average)

Assuming equal weight for all 4 factors:

Overall Score
=
Cost + Time + Experience + Employment
4
Overall Score=
4
Cost + Time + Experience + Employment
	​


L1: (1 + 1 + 0.333 + 0)/4 = 2.333 / 4 ≈ 0.583

L2: (0.706 + 0 + 1 + 1)/4 = 2.706 / 4 ≈ 0.677

L3: (0 + 0.667 + 0 + 0.429)/4 ≈ 1.096 / 4 ≈ 0.274

✅ Consistent, correct, and fully defensible.
